# Research Harness core rules

- Treat this workspace as the Research Harness control surface.
- For any research workflow, read `AGENTS.md` and `docs/agent-guide.md` when the relevant rule is not already in context.
- Use the `research-harness` MCP server for research primitives (`paper_search`, `paper_ingest`, `deep_read`, `claim_extract`, `gap_detect`, `baseline_identify`, `section_draft`, `orchestrator_*`).
- Do not run research primitives through `rh primitive ...`; CLI is only for data management/read-only checks such as topic/paper/status listing.
- Always specify `topic_id` for paper ingestion and analysis. Never create loose paper/PDF folders in the repo.
- Cursor is the preferred local client for paper deep reading on this machine; use the `rh-paper-deep-reader` subagent or `rh-paper-deep-reading` skill for 精读 tasks.
- Key outputs must be recorded through `orchestrator_record_artifact` when they affect the research state.
- Prefer Chinese responses for the human researcher unless they request another language.
- Never print or commit secrets from `.env`, Cursor auth files, or provider credentials.
